{
  "texts": [
    "Upon successful verification of crosschain requests by the miners of the relay chain R, the relay chain R returns a readiness confirmation, allowing subchains to upload multi-modal healthcare data (Step b in Fig. 1) [16].",
    "After transmitting the multi-modal healthcare data to the main chain M, the health center initiates MLLM training (Step c in Fig. 1).",
    "Once MLLM training is completed, the health center and hospitals can access the MLLM Application Programming Interface (API) or the weights file of MLLMs through the relay chain R (Step d in Fig. 1), and the health center rewards them with monetary compensation based on their data contribution (Step e in Fig.",
    "Hybrid RAG-empowered MLLM Framework for Data Management in IoMTData management tasks in hospitals and the health center include data storage, analysis, and retrieval.",
    "When multimodal healthcare data is gathered into the subchains, MLLMs categorize the data by type and store it in the appropriate databases."
  ]
}